article_title: Health-Care, Energy Shares Weigh on Market
article_text:
U.S. stock indexes ended marginally lower, weighed down by declines in health-care and energy shares.

The muted moves for major indexes followed the market’s biggest daily rally in nearly a month.

The Dow Jones Industrial Average inched down 4.41 points, little changed on a percentage basis, to 17732.75. The S&P 500 fell 2.34 points,...
